helming start and launched a jaw-dropping second throw from the Stade de France into the stratosphere, which looked promising as soon as it left his grip.\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an underwhelming start\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 347}, {\"ngram\": \"a jaw-dropping second throw\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 388}, {\"ngram\": \"the stratosphere\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 435}, {\"ngram\": \"his grip\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A huge roar echoed around the stadium as the javelin flew past the 90 metre mark and the 2022Commonwealth Gameschampion immediately raised his arms in the air in celebration.\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 664, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A huge roar\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"the javelin\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"the 90 metre mark\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 570}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022Commonwealth Gameschampion\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 609}, {\"ngram\": \"his arms\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official distance came back as 92.97m, surpassing Andreas Thorkildsen's previous Olympic record of 90.57m, set at the Beijing Games back in 2008.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Thorkildsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andreas Thorkildsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Thorkildsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andreas_Thorkildsen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The official distance\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 687}, {\"ngram\": \"92.97m\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"90.57m\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 775}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing Games\", \"from\": 784, \"to\": 801}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unsurprisingly, Nadeem's effort went unbeaten for the remaining rounds and India's Neeraj Chopra - the defending champion - had to settle for the silver medal.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.9934085430120708, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadeem\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadeem_Baig_(actor)\"}, {\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999974544223845, \"rank\": 2.5406526161232155e-06, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neeraj Chopra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the remaining rounds\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the defending champion\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze medal went to Anderson Peters, with the 26-year-old taking home Grenada's fifth medal in the history of the O